## Populating the PCB

When populating the PCB, there is a sequence that is highly recommended to follow. Components should be installed from flat (e.g., wire bridges, resistors, …) to tall (e.g., switches, capacitors, …). Next-to-last, solder on any connector leads—otherwise they may get in the way during assembly. The optical mouse sensor/processor is installed last.  
> :warning: Always solder one leg of a component first, then check its seating (e.g., ensure parts and wires lie cleanly on the PCB).

